    "body": "Same here with fish and starship. It seems that vscode terminal integration is using the VSCODE_ENV_PREPEND environment variable to prepend the PATH variable.\r\nWhen starship enabled, the env command displays the following lines:\r\n```sh\r\nVSCODE_ENV_PREPEND=PATH=/home/amtoaer/.vscode-server/extensions/ms-python.python-2024.0.1/pythonFiles/deactivate/fish\\x3a/home/amtoaer/.cache/pypoetry/virtualenvs/aaio-J_7VdAtR-py3.11/bin\\x3a\r\nPATH= {original PATH}\r\n```\r\nWhen disabled, only this line is visible:\r\n```\r\nPATH=/home/amtoaer/.vscode-server/extensions/ms-python.python-2024.0.1/pythonFiles/deactivate/fish:/home/amtoaer/.cache/pypoetry/virtualenvs/aaio-J_7VdAtR-py3.11/bin:{original PATH}\r\n```\r\nIt can be observed that, due to some unknown reasons, enabling starship causes vscode terminal integration's PATH prepend to not take effect. Here's what I found regarding vscode fish shell integration: [link](https://github.com/microsoft/vscode/blob/150d9e622b41ac36e186a6d7196dbaa36ccd5254/src/vs/workbench/contrib/terminal/browser/media/fish_xdg_data/fish/vendor_conf.d/shellIntegration.fish#L46).\r\nWould appreciate any insights or solutions to resolve this issue. (translated by ChatGPT.)",
