    "updated_at": "2024-03-16T15:37:12Z",
    "body": "@thatguy7 Hi, I found a workaround for this issue. Just add the following lines **after** `starship init fish | source`:\r\n```sh\r\n    if string match -q \"$TERM_PROGRAM\" \"vscode\"\r\n        set -e VSCODE_SHELL_INTEGRATION\r\n        . (code --locate-shell-integration-path fish)\r\n    end\r\n```\r\nIt appears that VS Code Fish integration has been initialized successfully, setting the VSCODE_SHELL_INTEGRATION flag. However, it doesn't seem to take effect due to Starship. Therefore, it's necessary to manually remove the VSCODE_SHELL_INTEGRATION flag and rerun the VS Code Fish integration. This solution works for me.",
    "author_association": "NONE",
